  "text": "Editorial Note: Talk Android may contain affiliate links on some articles. If you make a purchase through these links, we will earn a commission at no extra cost to you. Learn more. Everybody wants in on the modern take of the clamshell, or rather, flip phone, and if you've been waiting for the right deal at the right time, perhaps this is the offer for you. The unlocked version of Motorola's Razr 2023 is now discounted from its RRP of $699 to just $349.99, its lowest-ever price on Amazon. Powered by the Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 processor, the Razr 2023 packs 8GB RAM and 128GB of built-in storage. The internal P-OLED display unfolds into a big 6.9-inch panel with a 144Hz refresh rate, and the external AMOLED screen is 1.5-inch in size, great for checking notifications and such. The rear camera setup consists of a 64MP main lens and a 13MP ultra-wide lens, both of which are situated in the external display. A 32MP selfie camera is housed in a central punch-hole on the internal display. The 4,200mAh battery is good-sized and has 30W wired charging and 5W wireless charging. Unlike many of its rivals, the Razr 2023 also benefits from having a fast charger included in the box. In terms of security, the fingerprint scanner is incorporated into the power button on the side of the frame. Motorola Razr (2023)Size 170.82 x 73.95 x 7.35 mmWeight188.6gDisplay6.9-Inch P-OLED, 1080P, 144Hz1.5″ AMOLED cover screenProcessorQualcomm Snapdragon 7 Gen 1RAM8GBStorage128GBSoftwareAndroid 13Cameras64MP wide camera, f/1.7 aperture13MP ultra-wide camera, f/2.2 aperture32MP front cameraBattery Size4,200 mAhCharging SpeedsWired: 30.0WWireless: 5.0WColorsSage Green, Vanilla Cream, Summer Lilac, Grape Compote Software-wise, the Razr 2023 is scheduled to be updated to Android 16, with security patches rolling out for a year after that. It's not quite Samsung levels, but it's pretty good for Motorola. Available in a range of colorways, the Razr 2023 has an aluminum frame and a vegan leather finish, which means you won't have to worry about fingerprints. It's a stylish-looking phone, especially when it's closed into its clamshell. With an RRP of $699 and often discounted down to $400 on Amazon, according to CamelCamelCamel, the Razr 2023 is now on sale for just $349.99. This gives a further $50 saving, which means an overall discount of 50% on the $699 RRP. He's been an Android fan ever since owning an HTC Hero, with the Dell Streak being his first phablet. He currently carries an Honor Magic 5 Pro in his pockets, a Xiaomi Pad 5 in his backpack, and thinks nothing of lugging a 17-inch laptop around the world. When not immersed in the world of Android and gadgets, he's an avid sports fan, and like all South Africans, he loves a good Braai (BBQ). Previous Post",
