/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1.png 876w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1-701x635.png 701w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1-706x640.png 706w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1-380x344.png 380w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1-550x499.png 550w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Motorola-razr-2023-1-800x725.png 800w\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePowered by the \u003ca href=\"https://www.talkandroid.com/371891-qualcomm-snapdragon-8-gen-1-chip/\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"371891\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003eSnapdragon 8 Gen 1\u003c/a\u003e processor, the Razr 2023 packs 8GB RAM and 128GB of built-in storage. The internal P-OLED display unfolds into a big 6.9-inch panel with a 144Hz refresh rate, and the external AMOLED screen is 1.5-inch in size, great for checking notifications and such. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe rear camera setup consists of a 64MP main lens and a 13MP ultra-wide lens, both of which are situated in the external display. A 32MP selfie camera is housed in a central punch-hole on the internal display. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe 4,200mAh battery is good-sized and has 30W wired charging and 5W wireless charging. Unlike many of its rivals, the Razr 2023 also benefits from having a fast charger included in the box. In terms of security, the fingerprint scanner is incorporated into the power button on the side of the frame. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth\u003eMotorola Razr (2023)\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize\u003c/strong\u003e \u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e170.82 x 73.95 x 7.35 mm\u003cbr/\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWeight\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e188.6g\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisplay\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e6.9-Inch P-OLED, 1080P, 144Hz\u003cbr/\u003e1.5″ AMOLED cover screen\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProcessor\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eQualcomm Snapdragon 7 Gen 1\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRAM\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e8GB\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStorage\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e128GB\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSoftware\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eAndroid 13\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCameras\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e64MP wide camera, f/1.7 aperture\u003cbr/\u003e13MP ultra-wide camera, f/2.2 aperture\u003cp\u003e32MP front camera\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBattery Size\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e4,200 mAh\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharging Speeds\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eWired: 30.0W\u003cbr/\u003eWireless: 5.0W\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eColors\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eSage Green, Vanilla Cream, \u003cbr/\u003eSummer Lilac, Grape Compote\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eSoftware-wise, the Razr 2023 is scheduled to be updated to Android 16, with security patches rolling out for a year after that. It\u0026#39;s not quite Samsung levels, but it\u0026#39;s pretty good for Motorola. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAvailable in a range of colorways, the Razr 2023 has an aluminum frame and a vegan leather finish, which means you won\u0026#39;t have to worry about fingerprints. It\u0026#39;s a stylish-looking phone, especially when it\u0026#39;s closed into its clamshell.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith an RRP of $699 and often discounted down to $400 on Amazon, according to \u003ca href=\"https://camelcamelcamel.com/product/B0CGWDCS3L\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener follow external\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eCamelCamelCamel\u003c/a\u003e, the Razr 2023 is now on sale for just $349.99. This gives a further $50 saving, which means an overall discount of 50% on the $699 RRP. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eHe\u0026#39;s been an Android fan ever since owning an HTC Hero, with the Dell Streak being his first phablet. He currently carries an Honor Magic 5 Pro in his pockets, a Xiaomi Pad 5 in his backpack, and thinks nothing of lugging a 17-inch laptop around the world. When not immersed in the world of Android and gadgets, he\u0026#39;s an avid sports fan, and like all South Africans, he loves a good Braai (BBQ).\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch5\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePrevious Post\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h5\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv data-scheme=\"inverse\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg width=\"380\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/4-380x250.jpg\" alt=\"The Xiaomi 15 Series Is Here; The First Snapdragon 8 Elite Phones 8\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/4-380x250.jpg 380w, https://www.talkandroid.com/wp-content/uplo